From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Keyur Maru <kd2maru@gmail.com>
Date: Mon, 13 Jul 2026 05:28:11 -0700
Subject: [PATCH 2/2] init: force SELinux permissive on channel (bring-up; DROP
 before release)

channel boots the Android-17 system image on an Android-11-frozen vendor, and the
policy is still being triaged, so the device is run permissive for now. The usual
androidboot.selinux=permissive route does not work here: the bootloader appends
its own DTB bootargs after ours, and its cmdline wins, so init always sees an
enforcing request.

Short-circuit IsEnforcing() while ALLOW_PERMISSIVE_SELINUX is set (userdebug/eng
only; user builds still return true unconditionally). This commit is isolated so
it can be dropped once the denials are triaged and enforcing is revalidated.
---
 init/selinux.cpp | 8 ++++++--
 1 file changed, 6 insertions(+), 2 deletions(-)

diff --git a/init/selinux.cpp b/init/selinux.cpp
index 4baf9a4fe..5258f5eac 100644
--- a/init/selinux.cpp
+++ b/init/selinux.cpp
@@ -100,7 +100,7 @@ namespace {
 
 enum EnforcingStatus { SELINUX_PERMISSIVE, SELINUX_ENFORCING };
 
-EnforcingStatus StatusFromProperty() {
+[[maybe_unused]] EnforcingStatus StatusFromProperty() {
     std::string value;
     if (android::fs_mgr::GetKernelCmdline("androidboot.selinux", &value) && value == "permissive") {
         return SELINUX_PERMISSIVE;
@@ -113,7 +113,11 @@ EnforcingStatus StatusFromProperty() {
 
 bool IsEnforcing() {
     if (ALLOW_PERMISSIVE_SELINUX) {
-        return StatusFromProperty() == SELINUX_ENFORCING;
+        // BRING-UP / BRIDGE: force SELinux permissive. The LOS prebuilt kernel's appended-DTB
+        // bootargs override our boot.img androidboot.selinux=permissive, so the cmdline route
+        // doesn't take effect. Force permissive here to unblock the Android-17 boot on the
+        // legacy vendor while we triage denials. Remove to restore the line below for release.
+        return false;  // was: return StatusFromProperty() == SELINUX_ENFORCING;
     }
     return true;
 }
